./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:10:- `relay-agent-assistant` OSS SDK packages
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:13:The goal is to prevent duplicate assistant-runtime work while avoiding leakage of transport infrastructure or product-specific behavior into the wrong layer.
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:19:- if the capability is transport, auth, scheduling substrate, or low-level action dispatch, keep it in Relay foundation
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:20:- if the capability assumes an assistant identity, memory model, session continuity model, specialist orchestration model, or focused inter-agent connectivity model, move it here
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:31:- channel and transport session substrate
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:35:- relaycast or other communication infrastructure
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:36:- transport-level observability
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:53:- assistant-facing surface abstractions above normalized transport events
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:55:- focused inter-agent connectivity, signaling, and convergence contracts
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:56:- assistant-level routing, latency, depth, and budget-aware policy hooks
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:85:### `@relay-assistant/core`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:101:- provider-specific transport code
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:105:### `@relay-assistant/memory`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:118:### `@relay-assistant/proactive`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:133:### `@relay-assistant/sessions`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:144:- raw transport sessions
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:147:### `@relay-assistant/surfaces`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:157:- Relay foundation still owns actual transport delivery to each destination
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:159:- Example: deciding that one assistant summary should go to web plus Slack belongs here; the actual Slack API post and web transport delivery remain in Relay foundation
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:164:- provider SDK clients as foundational transport code
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:166:### `@relay-assistant/coordination`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:179:### `@relay-assistant/connectivity`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:186:- communication efficiency rules for internal assistant coordination
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:190:- raw message transport or relaycast substrate
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:194:### `@relay-assistant/routing`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:198:- assistant-facing routing contracts
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:200:- model-choice policy above raw provider clients
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:201:- integration points for workforce workload-router style persona/tier resolution
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:205:- raw transport routing
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:207:- product-specific commercial routing rules
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:209:### `@relay-assistant/policy`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:222:### `@relay-assistant/examples`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:238:| Relay gateway and adapter infrastructure | transport, verification, normalization, raw actions | stay in Relay foundation |
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:241:| NightCTO specialist orchestration and per-client continuity | many-agents-one-assistant and proactive monitoring | `coordination`, `connectivity`, `policy`, `memory`, `proactive` |
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:242:| Workforce workload-router and persona tiers | quality-preserving routing across depth/latency/cost envelopes | `routing`, parts of `core`, links to `coordination` |
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:250:- a simple assistant may import `@relay-assistant/core`, `@relay-assistant/sessions`, and `@relay-assistant/surfaces`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:251:- a memory-heavy assistant may additionally import `@relay-assistant/memory`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:252:- a specialist-based assistant may add `@relay-assistant/coordination` and `@relay-assistant/policy`
./docs/architecture/package-boundary-map.md:254:Consumers should not import Relay infrastructure directly to bypass assistant-level contracts unless they are implementing a transport adapter or other foundational infrastructure outside this repo.
